            <div class="col-md-4" style="height:650px;overflow:auto ; text-align:center ; border:solid black">
                <h3>Game rules</h3>
                <article>
                    <h4>Gladiator stats</h4>
                    <p>Health show how much damage your gladiator can take before losing.</p>
                    <p>Armor determine how hard it will be for opponent to hit you, players are limited to a max of 18 armor.</p>
                    <p>Damage dice show how many of what type of dice you roll to determine your damage.</p>
                    <p>Strenght will increase strenght modifyer that help increase both damage and hit chance.</p>
                    <p>Strenght modifyer is calculated "(Strenght - 10) / 2" and this is what is added onto damage and hit rolls.</p>
                    <p>Constitution increase constitution modifyer that will help increase your health. Each point added to constitution grants +1 health.</p>
                    <p>Constitution modifyer is calculated "(Constitution - 10) / 2" used in health calculation.</p>
                    <br />
                    <h4>Battle mechanics</h4>
                    <p>The Battle start with both fighters rolling a D20 (20 sided dice) ontop of this they add the strenght modifyer.</p>
                    <p>With this roll they gonna have to roll equal or higher then the opponents armor to hit.</p>
                    <p>If they hit they will roll 2 x D8 for damage then add the strenght modifyer to it.</p>
                    <p>Rolling a 20 on the D20 will make it a critical hit doubeling the damage.</p>
                    <p>If both misses they both recover 5 health.</p>
                    <br />
                    <h4>Leveling</h4>
                    <p>As the gladiator gain experiance they will level up. Each time a gladiator level up they will roll a D6 for added health
                    with the constitiution modifyer added onto it.</p>
                    <p>Each level allso grant 2 skill points that can be placed in armor , strenght or constitution.</p>
